    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-01-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="672"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">846G.79693/1–1548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-01-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 16, 1948—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>71. Pan Am issued instructions 15th to effect that company will in no way
                    voluntarily give up right carry traffic Hong Kong-Shanghai, urtel 99, Jan
                    15.</p>
                <p>While Dept hopes above will correct undesirable effect Pan Am action reported
                    urtel, point should be made clearly to Chinese that regardless of actions of
                    carrier US Govt alone is one to decide whether fifth freedom rights will be
                    exercised at least until outcome consultation with Chinese becomes known.</p>
                <p>Detailed comment urtel follows.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking as 71; rptd Shanghai as 88.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
